<Link id="l00119" /><CodeLine lineNumber="119"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00120" /><CodeLine lineNumber="120"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// A directive&#39;s supplied pattern is said to be either expected or excluded</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00121" /><CodeLine lineNumber="121"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// depending on whether the pattern must have or must not have a match in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00122" /><CodeLine lineNumber="122"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// order for the directive to succeed.  For example, a CHECK directive&#39;s</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="123"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// pattern is expected, and a CHECK-NOT directive&#39;s pattern is excluded.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="124"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="125"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// There might be more than one match result for a single pattern.  For</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="126"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// example, there might be several discarded matches</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="127"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// (MatchFoundButDiscarded) before either a good match</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="128"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// (MatchFoundAndExpected) or a failure to match (MatchNoneButExpected),</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="129"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// and there might be a fuzzy match (MatchFuzzy) after the latter.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
